There are here abundance of Civet Cats;
•• vit Cat. this is a ſmall Creature very like our Cats, only that its Noſe is ſomething ſharper, and its Claws not ſo dangerous; the Perfume which it produces is engendred in a ſmall opening, which is under its Tail; it appears not unlike a Greaſe, and is taken out from
thence by little and little at a time, and is repleniſhed according as the Civet Cat is well or ill fed. They drive a great trade in this Commodity at Calicut, but it is ſeldom to be got unfalſified, unleſs one have the opportunity of taking it out ones ſelf.
